====Noun====
{{en-noun}}
{{tearoom}}

# A large omnivorous mammal, related to the dog and raccoon, having shaggy hair, a very small tail, and flat feet.
# {{colloquial}} An animal that resembles a bear, such as a [[koala]], [[panda]], or [[sloth]]. <!-- FWIW, pandas are actually in the family Ursidae -->
# {{finance}} A [[market]] in which prices are falling.
# {{finance}} An [[investor]] who sells (commodities or securities) in anticipation of a fall in prices.
# {{colloquial}} A problem that is very difficult to solve.
# {{context|vulgar|Exchange Alley}} One who contracts to deliver a certain quantity or sum of stock in the public funds, on a future day, and at stated price; or, in other words, sells what he has not got, like the huntsman in the fable, who sold the bear’s skin before the bear was killed. As the bear sells the stock he does not possess, so the bull purchases what he has not money to pay for; but in case of any alteration in the price agreed on, either party pays or receives the difference.<!--is this different to the finance defintions above?-->
# {{slang}} A [[large]] [[hairy]] [[man]], especially one who is [[gay]].

